node.text: Emma and Nat of @littlepicklememories make inclusive keepsake products for all types of families—from LGBTQIA+ parents to single parents to adoptive parents. After their daughter was born, they struggled to find a baby memory book that didn’t say ‘mom’ and ‘dad’. So they decided to create their own, and eventually started a business. Watch to learn more about their inspiring story, then check out their Etsy shop: etsy.me/littlepicklememories

node.text: “My work centers Black joy, community, and love. I hope that it makes others feel seen, held, and welcome in all their complexities,” says Chiomma Hall of @chiommani. Watch to learn more about how her beautiful prints draw from the intersections of her identity to portray Black and LGBTQIA+ communities reveling in rest, choosing self-care, and communing with loved ones. Then visit her Etsy shop to admire her art: etsy.me/chiommani

This Hispanic Heritage Month, support multicultural, multi-talented makers. Sol of @solonline creates stunning home decor and jewelry pieces that combine her South American roots with American minimalistic style using mixed metals, leather, yarn, and silk.⁣
⁣
“I hope my pieces are a reminder for people to pause, take a deep breath, and take a moment to appreciate the magic that appears at any given instant. This world is hectic and crazy, and we all work hard, but it's also beautiful. I think everyone deserves a daily pause to enjoy it.” ✨⁣
⁣
Head to our link in bio to admire her work and discover more inspiring finds from our Hispanic, Latino, Latina, and Latinx sellers.
